main event: On 23 September 1957 in Virginia Beach, Oceana Va., civilians reported sighting a round, silver white object that lit up brilliantly for several seconds, before moving rapidly to the east.
interesting points: The object was described as a round, silver white object that lit up periodically and moved rapidly to the east.
There was no length of observation reported for this sighting.
The report suggested possible aircraft, probable aircraft, or inadequate data for evaluation as conclusions.
The sighting was not reported until 15 minutes after the object was sighted as per the balloon schedule check.
No photographs were taken of the object.
sighted object: round, silver white object that lit up periodically
